<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,431,743,768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Male (female unknown): ventral margin of IV­L­4 with two long setae; setae at the ventral margin of IV­L­5 distant, a thickened, wavy­proximal seta orginating on a ventroproximal projection of IV­L­5, the distal sword­shaped seta exceeding distal margin of IV­L­5; ventral side of I­L­5 with one seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" box="[312,458,903,929]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,450,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Description</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,382,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Male:</emphasis>
Dorsal and ventral shields present; dorsal shield bearing nine pairs of glandularia (
<figureCitation box="[332,404,983,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–13" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,435,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-88@6.[277,1310,430,1774]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–13. Kongsbergia persica sp. nov., male: 7 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 8 = idiosoma, ventral view; 9 = palp, lateral view; 10 = palp, medial view; 11 = IV­L­4/6; 12 = IV­L; 13 = I­L­2/6. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050345/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); dorsal shield L 335, W 195; ventral shield (
<figureCitation box="[936,1006,983,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–13" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,435,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-88@6.[277,1310,430,1774]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–13. Kongsbergia persica sp. nov., male: 7 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 8 = idiosoma, ventral view; 9 = palp, lateral view; 10 = palp, medial view; 11 = IV­L­4/6; 12 = IV­L; 13 = I­L­2/6. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050345/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) L 373, W 241; extensions at insertions of the fourth legs pointed, extending laterally to the body proper; two rows of acetabula extending along sides of body from gonopore; excretory pore located near posterior end of dorsal shield slightly anterior to the gonopore; gnathosoma L 86; palp (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7–13" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,435,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-88@6.[277,1310,430,1774]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–13. Kongsbergia persica sp. nov., male: 7 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 8 = idiosoma, ventral view; 9 = palp, lateral view; 10 = palp, medial view; 11 = IV­L­4/6; 12 = IV­L; 13 = I­L­2/6. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050345/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 9­ 10</figureCitation>
): total L 225, dL and relative L (in parentheses given as % of total length): P­1 19 (8.4), P­2 62 (27.6), P­3 32 (14.2), P­4 75 (33.3), P­5 37 (16.4); ventral side of P­2 with one large tubercle, and three or four smaller tubercles which are more anteriorly placed; dorsal lengths (segments 1­6 IV­L): 94, 96, 69, 107, 84, 93; ventral margin of IV­L­4 with two long setae; IV­L­5 with particular modifications in shape and setation as depicted in the figures 11­12 and described in the diagnosis, the proximal seta, L/W 58/21, the distal seta, L/W 52/10; ventral side of I­L­5 with one sword like seta (
<figureCitation box="[954,1040,1383,1409]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–13" captionStartId="6.[264,383,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[300,1295,435,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-88@6.[277,1310,430,1774]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–13. Kongsbergia persica sp. nov., male: 7 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 8 = idiosoma, ventral view; 9 = palp, lateral view; 10 = palp, medial view; 11 = IV­L­4/6; 12 = IV­L; 13 = I­L­2/6. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050345/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" box="[312,532,1423,1449]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,400,1423,1448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,440,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei, 2005" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei" authorityYear="2005" box="[460,708,1463,1488]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[460,708,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Kongsbergia persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[720,815,1463,1489]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
seems very closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter, 1930" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1930" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruttneri">
<emphasis box="[1194,1322,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. ruttneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walter, C." box="[264,417,1503,1529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="180 - 192" refId="ref4456" refString="Walter, C. 1930 Neue Hydracarinen aus dem Genus Kongsbergia und die Synonymie von Hjartdalia Thor und Kongsbergia Thor. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 91, 180 - 192." type="journal article" year="1930">Walter, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis box="[482,621,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. d­motasi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T." box="[629,1065,1503,1529]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="293 - 333" refId="ref3812" refString="Motas, C., Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T. (1958) Hydrachnelles phreaticoles de la R. P. Roumaine. Vestnik Ceholovenske Zoologiske Spolecnosti, 22, 293 - 333." type="journal article" year="1958">Motas, Tanasachi &amp; Orghidan, 1958</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei, 2005" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei" authorityYear="2005" box="[1077,1323,1503,1528]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1077,1323,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Kongsbergia persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,356,1543,1569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can easily be distingushed from both of these species by the presence of a more elongated wavy­proximal seta at the ventral margin of IV­L­5 (more roundish in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1930" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruttneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. ruttneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see: 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter, C." box="[380,526,1623,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="180 - 192" refId="ref4456" refString="Walter, C. 1930 Neue Hydracarinen aus dem Genus Kongsbergia und die Synonymie von Hjartdalia Thor und Kongsbergia Thor. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 91, 180 - 192." type="journal article" year="1930">Walter 1930</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T." box="[537,742,1623,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref3781" refString="Motas, C., Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T. (1947) Hydracariens phreaticoles de Roumanie. Notationes Biologicae, 5, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1947">Motas et al. 1947</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwoerbel, J." box="[754,962,1623,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="33 - 43" refId="ref4211" refString="Schwoerbel, J. (1962) Subterrane Susswassermilben (Hydrachnellae) aus dem Bregenzer Wald. Beitrage zur Naturkundlichen Forschung in Sudwestdeutschland, 21, 33 - 43." type="journal article" year="1962">Schwoerbel 1962</bibRefCitation>
); club­shaped and shorter in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. d­motasi</emphasis>
(see: 
<bibRefCitation author="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T." box="[438,647,1663,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="293 - 333" refId="ref3812" refString="Motas, C., Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T. (1958) Hydrachnelles phreaticoles de la R. P. Roumaine. Vestnik Ceholovenske Zoologiske Spolecnosti, 22, 293 - 333." type="journal article" year="1958">Motas et al. 1958</bibRefCitation>
). Further differences are found in a shorter sword­shaped seta at the ventral margin of IV­L­5 (not exceeding distal margins of IV­L­5) and presence of two setae at the ventral margin of I­L­ 
<quantity box="[756,801,1743,1769]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1930" box="[810,936,1743,1768]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruttneri">
<emphasis box="[810,936,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. ruttneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see: 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwoerbel, J." box="[1008,1218,1743,1769]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="33 - 43" refId="ref4211" refString="Schwoerbel, J. (1962) Subterrane Susswassermilben (Hydrachnellae) aus dem Bregenzer Wald. Beitrage zur Naturkundlichen Forschung in Sudwestdeutschland, 21, 33 - 43." type="journal article" year="1962">Schwoerbel 1962</bibRefCitation>
); ventral margin of IV­L­5 with proximal and distal setae close to each other and a much larger palp (palp total L 328) in 
<emphasis box="[508,644,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">K. d­motasi</emphasis>
(measurement in parentheses, from 
<bibRefCitation author="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T." box="[1071,1278,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" pagination="293 - 333" refId="ref3812" refString="Motas, C., Tanasachi, J. &amp; Orghidan, T. (1958) Hydrachnelles phreaticoles de la R. P. Roumaine. Vestnik Ceholovenske Zoologiske Spolecnosti, 22, 293 - 333." type="journal article" year="1958">Motas et al. 1958</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,623,1889]" box="[312,1106,1863,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[312,437,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Etymology</emphasis>
: The species is named for its occurrence in 
<collectingCountry box="[952,999,1863,1889]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1015,1093,1863,1889]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Persia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1322,284,390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[312,403,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Biology</emphasis>
: As suggested by the single known record, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei, 2005" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori &amp; Asadi &amp; Vafaei" authorityYear="2005" box="[932,1055,284,309]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[932,1055,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">K. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1064,1157,284,310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is probably a hyporheobiontic species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1322,284,390]" box="[312,945,364,390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[312,455,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Distribution</emphasis>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[470,520,364,390]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Iran</collectingCountry>
, only known from the 
<emphasis box="[786,938,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">locus typicus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
